value.value: This gene is involved in transcriptional regulation and signaling pathway modulation.

Human GLIS2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 16p13.3 and is approximately 25 kb in length. This allele, which encodes zinc finger protein GLIS2, plays a role in the modulation of both signaling and transcription. Mutation of the gene is associated with type 7 nephronophthisis.
Zinc finger protein GLIS2 (524 aa, ~56 kDa) is encoded by the human GLIS2 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of transcription and the repression of signaling pathways.
A protein encoded by the PPBP gene.
A classification scheme in which gastric adenocarcinomas are separated into diffuse adenocarcinoma, intestinal type adenocarcinoma, mixed adenocarcinoma, or indeterminate type adenocarcinoma.
Cytochrome P450 2A6 (494 aa, ~57 kDa) is encoded by the human CYP2A6 gene. This protein is involved in the metabolism of xenobiotics.
A variation in the amino acid sequence for the tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2 protein.
A genetic profile indicating low expression of cellular tight junction proteins, including E-cadherin, which is often associated with triple-negative breast cancer and tumor-infiltrating lymphocytes.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 617 in the tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2 protein where valine has been replaced by phenylalanine.
A complex substitution where the nucleotide sequence at positions 1848 and 1849 of the coding sequence of the JAK2 gene has changed from thymine-guanine to cytosine-thymine.
A nucleotide substitution at position 1849 of the coding sequence of the JAK2 gene where guanine has been mutated to thymine.
A nucleotide substitution at position 2792 of the coding sequence of the JAK2 gene where adenine has been mutated to guanine.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 931 in the tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2 protein where tyrosine has been replaced by cysteine.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 985 in the tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2 protein where glutamic acid has been replaced by lysine.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 935 in the tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2 protein where glycine has been replaced by arginine.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 960 in the tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2 protein where isoleucine has been replaced by valine.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 929 in the tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2 protein where methionine has been replaced by isoleucine.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 938 in the tyrosine-protein kinase JAK2 protein where arginine has been replaced by leucine.
This gene plays a role in epithelial cell growth.

Human EPGN wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4q13.3 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes epigen protein, is involved in epidermal cell survival, proliferation, and migration.
Epigen (154 aa, ~17 kDa) is encoded by the human EPGN gene. This protein plays a role in survival, proliferation, and migration of epidermal cells.
A chromosome band present on 5p.
This gene has activity as a protease inhibitor.

Human A2M wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12p13.31 and is approximately 49 kb in length. This allele, which encodes alpha-2-macroglobulin protein, plays a role in various processes as a protease inhibitor. Mutations in this gene are associated with alpha-2-macroglobulin deficiency and susceptibility to Alzheimer disease.
Alpha-2-macroglobulin (1474 aa, ~163 kDa) is encoded by the human A2M gene. This protein has activity as a protease inhibitor.
This gene is involved in serine/threonine mannosylation.

Human TMTC1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12p11.22 and is approximately 284 kb in length. This allele, which encodes transmembrane and TPR repeat-containing protein 1, a mitochondrial integral membrane protein of unknown function.
Protein O-mannosyl-transferase TMTC1 (882 aa, ~99 kDa) is encoded by the human TMTC1 gene. This protein is involved in protein mannosylation.
This gene is involved in cell signaling.

Human EDNRB wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 13q22 and is approximately 24 kb in length. This allele, which encodes endothelin receptor type B protein, plays a role in vasoconstriction, vasodilation, bronchoconstriction and cell proliferation. Mutations in this gene are associated with ABCD syndrome, Waardenburg syndrome, type 4A, and susceptibility to Hirschsprung disease 2.
Endothelin receptor type B (442 aa, ~50 kDa) is encoded by the human EDNRB gene. This protein is involved in vasoconstriction and vasodilation.
This gene plays a role in the reorganization of the actin cytoskeleton.

Human FGD5 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3p25.1 and is approximately 116 kb in length. This allele, which encodes FYVE, RhoGEF and PH domain-containing protein 5, is involved in both signal transduction and the reorganization of the actin cytoskeleton.

label.value: FYVE, RhoGEF and PH Domain-Containing Protein 5

value.value: FYVE, RhoGEF and PH domain-containing protein 5 (1462 aa, ~160 kDa) is encoded by the human FGD5 gene. This protein plays a role in both signal transduction and the reorganization of the actin cytoskeleton.
This gene is involved in the regulation of transcription.

Human LDB2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4p16 and is approximately 397 kb in length. This allele, which encodes LIM domain-binding protein 2, plays a role in the modulation of gene transcription.
LIM domain-binding protein 2 (373 aa, ~43 kDa) is encoded by the human LDB2 gene. This protein is involved in transcription factor regulation.
This gene may play a role in plasma membrane dynamics.
Human PALMD wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p22-p21 and is approximately 49 kb in length. This allele, which encodes palmdelphin protein, may be involved in plasma membrane dynamics.
Palmdelphin (551 aa, ~63 kDa) is encoded by the human PALMD gene. This protein may play a role in plasma membrane dynamics.

A family of apolipoproteins that are associated with high-density lipoprotein particles in the serum. These proteins may play a role in both the acute-phase of inflammation and in cholesterol transport.
This gene is involved in the metabolism of diacylglycerol.

Human PLPP3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p32.2 and is approximately 151 kb in length. This allele, which encodes phospholipid phosphatase 3 protein, plays a role in both diacylglycerol metabolism and phospholipase D cell signaling.
Phospholipid phosphatase 3 (311 aa, ~35 kDa) is encoded by the human PLPP3 gene. This protein is involved in both cell signaling and diacylglycerol metabolism.
This gene may play a role in both signaling and organogenesis.
